post_cb({"3817246": {"CommentCount": "1", "AcceptedAnswerId": "3817365", "LastEditDate": "2010-09-28T21:45:22.853", "LastEditorUserId": "210102", "CreationDate": "2010-09-28T21:40:55.013", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-28T22:20:24.043", "PostTypeId": "1", "ViewCount": "2421", "FavoriteCount": "1", "Title": "Assignment and comparison", "Id": "3817246", "OwnerUserId": "232918", "Body": "<p>Looking at the code:</p>\n<pre><code>int i = 5;\nif (i = 0)\n{\n  printf (\"Got here\\n\");\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>What does the C standard have to say about what will get printed? \nOr in more general terms does the assignment happen first or the comparison?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c>", "Score": "4", "AnswerCount": "9"}, "3817260": {"ParentId": "3817246", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>Assignment first, as it is part of the evaluation. The expression of the assignment returns the assigned value, so the expression evaluates as false.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "255313", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "3817260", "Score": "5", "CreationDate": "2010-09-28T21:43:56.460", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-28T21:43:56.460"}, "bq_ids": {"n4659": {"so_3817246_3817365_0": {"section_id": 7675, "quality": 0.5294117647058824, "length": 9}}}, "3817261": {"ParentId": "3817246", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>The expression of the if clause is evaluated first, the result of which is 0. </p>\n<p>This program will never print \"Got here\\n\".</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "126769", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "3817261", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2010-09-28T21:43:58.143", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-28T21:43:58.143"}, "3817257": {"ParentId": "3817246", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>The assignment happens, which returns a 0, which is false.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "20862", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "3817257", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2010-09-28T21:43:33.150", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-28T21:43:33.150"}, "3817365": {"ParentId": "3817246", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>\u00a76.8.4 says that the syntax for an <code>if</code> selection statement is:</p>\n<pre><b>if</b> ( expression ) <i>statement</i></pre>\n<p>Further in this section, it mentions that if the expression compares unequal to 0, then <em><code>statement</code></em> is executed. The expression must therefore be evaluated before it can be compared to 0. <code>i = 0</code> is an expression which evaluates to 0. For further reference, see \u00a76.5 \u201cExpressions\u201d with regards to \u00a76.5.16 \u201cAssignment operators\u201d, in particular note this excerpt:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_3817246_3817365_0\">An assignment operator stores a value in the object designated by the left operand. An\n  assignment expression has the value of the left operand after the assignment, but is not an lvalue.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "10320", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "3817365", "Score": "10", "CreationDate": "2010-09-28T22:04:41.893", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-28T22:04:41.893"}, "3817274": {"ParentId": "3817246", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>As others already said, the assignment returns the value of that is assigned and so never prints the statement. If you wanted the statement to be printed, you'd have to use <code>if (i = -1)</code>.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "34065", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "3817274", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2010-09-28T21:46:40.677", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-28T21:46:40.677"}, "3817439": {"ParentId": "3817246", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p><em>When the assignment happens</em> is irrelevant. What's relevant is the value of <code>i=0</code> as an expression, and it's defined to have the value 0.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "379897", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "3817439", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2010-09-28T22:20:24.043", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-28T22:20:24.043"}, "3817262": {"ParentId": "3817246", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "5", "Body": "<p><code>i=0</code> evaluates to 0 thus the output will not happen.  </p>\n<p>The prior assignment (the first line of source code) is irrelevant to the outcome.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "210102", "LastEditorUserId": "210102", "LastEditDate": "2010-09-28T22:13:57.337", "Id": "3817262", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2010-09-28T21:44:03.807", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-28T22:13:57.337"}, "3817263": {"ParentId": "3817246", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>The statement <code>i = 0</code> will be evaluated and return <code>0</code>, so the statement will not be printed.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "454545", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "3817263", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2010-09-28T21:44:05.693", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-28T21:44:05.693"}, "3817283": {"ParentId": "3817246", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Nothing will print. The 0 get assigned to i and then that value is tested for the condition.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "120753", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "3817283", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2010-09-28T21:48:16.330", "LastActivityDate": "2010-09-28T21:48:16.330"}});